                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>On the north wall of the central shrine in the Vṛishabhapurīśvara temple.</p>						
                            
                            <p>Rājarāja I. Year 23: 1007-08 A.D.</p>						
                            
                            <p>This inscription commences with the <hi rend="italic">praśasti, Tirumagaḷ pōla</hi>, etc., of Rājarāja I.</p>						
                            
                            <p>It records the arrangement made for the distribution of wages to the various servants in the temple of god Tiruttāntōṉṟi-Mahādēva in the eastern division of Śiṅgapura-nāḍu maintained by the <hi rend="italic">kāttār</hi> (?) of Puduppāḍi-kkallēri <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Iravikula māṇikkapuram, by Valivalaṅgiḻāṉ Vēḷāṉ Sūriyaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Sundara-śōḻa Mūvēndavēḷāṉ.</p>						
                            
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
